    <sys:String x:Key="LOCEmuWizardIntro">This wizard will guide you through a process of console emulator download and import, as well as import of emulated games.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="LOCEmuWizardNotice">Keep in mind that you can always add additional emulators and/or games later via main menu (under "Tools" menu for Emulator settings and "Add Games" menu for emulated games).</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="LOCEmuWizardDownloadListIntro" xml:space="preserve">Following is the list of emulators Playnite can recognize and automatically configure. You can download and install them by visiting their website. Once you have emulators installed, proceed to next screen to import them into Playnite.
        
You can also configure and import any custom emulator later via configuration menu.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="LOCEmuWizardEmuImportIntro">You can import any emulators installed on your PC by pressing "Autodetect from folder..." button. Playnite will search selected folder for any known emulators and provide option to import them. You can import from multiple folders by using said button multiple times, emulators will be added at the bottom of current list.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="LOCEmuWizardGameImportIntro">You can import games by pressing "Scan folder using Emulator" button. Selecting appropriate emulator will tell Playnite, which file types should be scanned and imported. You can import from multiple folders by using said button multiple times, games will be added at the bottom of current list.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="LOCEmuWizardNoEmulatorWarning">There are no emulators selected for import. You won't be able to automatically import any emulated games without configuring emulators first. Are you sure you want to continue and exit import process?</sys:String>
